Police Minister Bheki Cele is at former President Jacob Zuma’s home in Nkandla this afternoon. However, details pertaining to the reasons behind his visit remain sketchy. Over the past few days, the former President has been receiving a number of visitors, including politicians. On Monday, Zuma snubbed the Commission of Inquiry into allegations of State Capture, saying there is a level of bias against him and a lack of impartiality. Police minister Bheki Cele visits former president Jacob Zuma:  The State Capture Commission Chair, Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo, announced that the commission will go back to the Constitutional Court to seek an order for the arrest of the former president. Since then, members of uMkhonto Wesizwe Military Veterans Association have been camping outside Zuma’s homestead. Below is the letter from Zuma’s lawyers:  